<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>News Feed - SURF Example</title>
    <style>
        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
            color: #eee;
            padding: 2rem;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            color: #00d4ff;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .subtitle {
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .explanation {
            background: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.1);
            border: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.3);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: #a78bfa;
        }

        .explanation strong {
            color: #00d4ff;
        }

        .controls {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        button {
            padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .btn-primary {
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #00d4ff);
            color: white;
        }

        .btn-secondary {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            color: #888;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
        }

        button:hover {
            opacity: 0.9;
            transform: translateY(-1px);
        }

        .status {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .status.active {
            color: #22c55e;
        }

        /* News Feed Styles */
        .news-feed {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 0.75rem;
        }

        .feed-header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 0.5rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .update-time {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .news-item {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 1rem;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .news-item:hover {
            border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
        }

        .news-item.breaking {
            border-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.5);
            background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
        }

        .news-header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .category {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
            color: #00d4ff;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        .category.breaking {
            background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3);
            color: #ef4444;
        }

        .time {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .news-title {
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: #eee;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .news-title:hover {
            color: #00d4ff;
        }

        .read-indicator {
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: #22c55e;
        }

        .loading {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .back {
            position: fixed;
            top: 1rem;
            left: 1rem;
            color: #888;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .back:hover {
            color: #fff;
        }

        .news-item[data-read="true"] {
            opacity: 0.7;
        }

        .news-item[data-read="true"] .news-title {
            color: #666;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <a href="/examples/02-server-data" class="back">‚Üê Back</a>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>üì∞ News Feed with Server Sync</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">d-auto-refresh + d-action pattern</p>

        <div class="explanation">
            <strong>üîë Declarative Pattern:</strong> Click on news titles to mark as "read".
            <br><br>
            <strong>SURF handles:</strong>
            <ol style="margin-left: 1rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
                <li><code>d-auto-refresh</code> polls server every 5 seconds</li>
                <li><code>d-pulse="action"</code> sends POST on click</li>
                <li>Echo preserves read state across refreshes</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="status" id="status">Auto-refreshing every 5 seconds</div>

        <!-- Surface with auto-refresh - NO JS needed! -->
        <div id="news-surface" d-auto-refresh="5000" d-auto-refresh-url="/api/news">
            <div class="loading">Loading news feed...</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="/dist/surf.min.js"></script>
    <script>
        // Minimal JS: just update status on patch
        Surf.on('after:patch', () => {
            document.getElementById('status').textContent =
                'Updated at ' + new Date().toLocaleTimeString();
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>